	      	<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><font size="+2">Welcome to Epic Shadows</font></b></font>
			<p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
				Epic Shadows is a collection of dedicated fighters, casters and tradesmen who belong to the Vazaelle EverQuest server.  We stand for supporting each other, and helping everyone have the best EQ experience on the net.  Our officers and others organize raids and guild activities to build strong bonds between each member, and we also contribute our all to the groups that we join.
			</font></p>
			<p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
				We search for those who are dedicated to their groups and to their own progression.  We support you and invite you to join us.  Send us an e-mail if you are considering joining our Legion of Shadows. (<a href="mailto:ludarian@hotmail.com">E-mail Ludarian</a>)
			</font></p>
			
			<p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Results from Nagafen's Lair:<br>
			
			<table width="80%" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
					<tr bgcolor="AAAAAA">
						<td><font color="black">
							&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I think the best way to describe our raid on Sol B:  A learning experience!  We learned that staying by the zone isn't smart; it's train happy.  Also, the noxious spider is capable of taking out two full groups of lvl 35+.  I learned that Quendin is one of the most dedicated players I've ever met because even though he was hit with death a few times, he never complained and stuck the whole way through to make sure everyone was rezzed.  We did get two staves of writhing from the Noble, and Pludar ended up with golden chitin bracer from the nox spider (which I'm still trying to get him to sell me =).  I do believe the next time we go there we will be a little bit more informed on the zone and will be able to have success.  Plus, the levels we gain between now and then will help as well...
<br>
<br>
-Ludarian
						</font></td>
					</tr>
			</table>
			<p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Results from Sol A:<br>
			
			<table width="80%" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
					<tr bgcolor="AAAAAA">
						<td><font color="black">
							&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Sol A raid was great in my opinion.  The experience gained was good as well as some fairly decent loot for us lower levels.  Our group was composed of two visitors who enjoyed the experience as well.  A HUGE THANK YOU goes out to Elles and her assistance in rezing our group.  As well as Flyxen for his help in locating my corpse which was buried in the floor :P.  
<br>
<br>
-Keiri
						</font></td>
					</tr>
